What is the purpose of the if statement in this code?
fn main() {
    let condition = true;
    let number = if condition {
        5
    } else {
        6
    };

    if number == 5 {
        println!('condition was true and number is {}', number);
    }
},"It is used to conditionally assign a value to the variable number."

What is the value of the variable number if the condition is true?
fn main() {
    let condition = true;
    let number = if condition {
        5
    } else {
        6
    };

    if number == 5 {
        println!('condition was true and number is {}', number);
    }
},"It is 5."

